  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House", 
    "date": "2017-11-02T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Better Evaluation of Science and Technology Act or the BEST Act\n\nThis bill requires a federal agency, to the extent it is making a decision based on science when issuing a rule, to use scientific information, technical procedures, methods, protocols, methodologies, or models in a manner that is consistent with the best available science and the intended use of the information, based on the weight of the scientific evidence.\n\nEach federal agency shall make available to the public: (1) all of its notices, determinations, findings, rules, consent agreements, and orders in connection with a rule; (2) a nontechnical summary of each risk evaluation conducted in connection with a rule; and (3) a list of the studies considered by the agency in carrying out each evaluation, along with the results of those studies."
  }, 
